        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 6 at 4:48PM EDT by NWS Jackson KY</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Spruce Pine, or near Harlan, moving southeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harlan, Loyall, Evarts, Wallins Creek, Bobs Creek, Sandy Fork,
Bledsoe, Mary Alice, Chevrolet, Coldiron, Beverly, Black Snake,
Saylor, Elcomb, Napier, White Star, Black Mountain, Blackmont,
Warbranch, and Rosspoint.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
